Metrics.Name: % Exit
Metrics.Description: The percentage of exits from your property that occurred out of the total page views.

Metrics.Name: % New Sessions
Metrics.Description: The percentage of sessions by people who had never visited your property before.

Metrics.Name: % Search Exits
Metrics.Description: The percentage of searches that resulted in an immediate exit from your property.

Metrics.Name: % Search Refinements
Metrics.Description: The percentage of number of times a refinement (i.e., transition) occurs between internal search keywords within a session.

Metrics.Name: % Sessions with Search
Metrics.Description: The percentage of sessions with search.

Metrics.Name: Abandoned Funnels
Metrics.Description: The overall number of times users started goals without actually completing them.

Metrics.Name: Actions Per Social Session
Metrics.Description: The number of social interactions per session on your property.

Metrics.Name: AdSense Ad Units Viewed
Metrics.Description: The number of AdSense ad units viewed. An Ad unit is a set of ads displayed as a result of one piece of the AdSense ad code. Details: https://support.google.com/adsense/answer/32715?hl=en

Metrics.Name: AdSense Ads Clicked
Metrics.Description: The number of times AdSense ads on your site were clicked.

Metrics.Name: AdSense CTR
Metrics.Description: The percentage of page impressions that resulted in a click on an AdSense ad.

Metrics.Name: AdSense eCPM
Metrics.Description: The estimated cost per thousand page impressions. It is your AdSense Revenue per 1000 page impressions.

Metrics.Name: AdSense Exits
Metrics.Description: The number of sessions that ended due to a user clicking on an AdSense ad.

Metrics.Name: AdSense Impressions
Metrics.Description: The number of AdSense ads viewed. Multiple ads can be displayed within an Ad Unit.

Metrics.Name: AdSense Page Impressions
Metrics.Description: The number of pageviews during which an AdSense ad was displayed. A page impression can have multiple Ad Units.

Metrics.Name: AdSense Revenue
Metrics.Description: The total revenue from AdSense ads.

Metrics.Name: Average Order Value
Metrics.Description: The average revenue for an e-commerce transaction.

Metrics.Name: Average Price
Metrics.Description: The average revenue per item.

Metrics.Name: Average QTY
Metrics.Description: The average quantity of this item (or group of items) sold per purchase.

Metrics.Name: Average Search Depth
Metrics.Description: The average number of pages people viewed after performing a search on your property.

Metrics.Name: Avg. Document Content Loaded Time (sec)
Metrics.Description: The average time (in seconds) it takes the browser to parse the document.

Metrics.Name: Avg. Document Interactive Time (sec)
Metrics.Description: The average time (in seconds) it takes the browser to parse the document and execute deferred and parser-inserted scripts including the network time from the user's location to your server.

Metrics.Name: Avg. Domain Lookup Time (sec)
Metrics.Description: The average amount of time (in seconds) spent in DNS lookup for this page.

Metrics.Name: Avg. Page Download Time (sec)
Metrics.Description: The average amount of time (in seconds) to download this page.

Metrics.Name: Avg. Page Load Time (sec)
Metrics.Description: The average amount of time (in seconds) it takes for pages from the sample set to load, from initiation of the pageview (e.g. click on a page link) to load completion in the browser.

Metrics.Name: Avg. Redirection Time (sec)
Metrics.Description: The average amount of time (in seconds) spent in redirects before fetching this page. If there are no redirects, the value for this metric is expected to be 0.

Metrics.Name: Avg. Server Connection Time (sec)
Metrics.Description: The average amount of time (in seconds) spent in establishing TCP connection for this page.

Metrics.Name: Avg. Server Response Time (sec)
Metrics.Description: The average amount of time (in seconds) your server takes to respond to a user request, including the network time from user's location to your server.

Metrics.Name: Avg. Session Duration
Metrics.Description: The average duration of user sessions represented in total seconds.

Metrics.Name: Avg. Time on Page
Metrics.Description: The average amount of time users spent viewing this page or a set of pages.

Metrics.Name: Avg. Time on Screen
Metrics.Description: The average amount of time users spent on a screen in seconds.

Metrics.Name: Avg. User Timing (sec)
Metrics.Description: The average amount of elapsed time.

Metrics.Name: Avg. Value
Metrics.Description: The average value of an event.

Metrics.Name: Bounce Rate
Metrics.Description: The percentage of single-page session (i.e., session in which the person left your property from the first page).

Metrics.Name: Bounces
Metrics.Description: The total number of single page (or single engagement hit) sessions for your property.

Metrics.Name: Buy-to-Detail Rate
Metrics.Description: Unique purchases divided by views of product detail pages (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Cart-to-Detail Rate
Metrics.Description: Product adds divided by views of product details (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Clicks
Metrics.Description: The total number of times users have clicked on an ad to reach your property.

Metrics.Name: Correlation Score
Metrics.Description: Correlation Score for related products.

Metrics.Name: Cost
Metrics.Description: Derived cost for the advertising campaign. The currency for this value is based on the currency that you set in your AdWords account.

Metrics.Name: Cost per Conversion
Metrics.Description: The cost per conversion (including ecommerce and goal conversions) for your property.

Metrics.Name: Cost per Goal Conversion
Metrics.Description: The cost per goal conversion for your property.

Metrics.Name: Cost per Transaction
Metrics.Description: The cost per transaction for your property.

Metrics.Name: CPC
Metrics.Description: Cost to advertiser per click.

Metrics.Name: CPM
Metrics.Description: Cost per thousand impressions.

Metrics.Name: Crashes
Metrics.Description: The number of exceptions where isFatal is set to true.

Metrics.Name: Crashes / Screen
Metrics.Description: The number of fatal exceptions thrown divided by the number of screenviews.

Metrics.Name: CTR
Metrics.Description: Click-through-rate for your ad. This is equal to the number of clicks divided by the number of impressions for your ad (e.g. how many times users clicked on one of your ads where that ad appeared).

Metrics.Name: Custom Metric XX Value
Metrics.Description: The name of the requested custom metric, where XX refers the number/index of the custom metric.

Metrics.Name: Data Hub Activities
Metrics.Description: The count of activities where a content URL was shared / mentioned on a social data hub partner network.

Metrics.Name: Document Content Loaded Time (ms)
Metrics.Description: The time the browser takes (in milliseconds) to parse the document and execute deferred and parser-inserted scripts (DOMContentLoaded), including the network time from the user's location to your server. Parsing of the document is finished, the Document Object Model is ready, but referenced style sheets, images, and subframes may not be finished loading. This event is often the starting point for javascript framework execution, e.g., JQuery's onready() callback, etc.

Metrics.Name: Document Interactive Time (ms)
Metrics.Description: The time the browser takes (in milliseconds) to parse the document (DOMInteractive), including the network time from the user's location to your server. At this time, the user can interact with the Document Object Model even though it is not fully loaded.

Metrics.Name: DOM Latency Metrics Sample
Metrics.Description: The sample set (or count) of pageviews used to calculate the averages for site speed DOM metrics. This metric is used in the avgDomContentLoadedTime and avgDomInteractiveTime calculations.

Metrics.Name: Domain Lookup Time (ms)
Metrics.Description: The total amount of time (in milliseconds) spent in DNS lookup for this page among all samples.

Metrics.Name: Ecommerce Conversion Rate
Metrics.Description: The average number of transactions for a session on your property.

Metrics.Name: Entrances
Metrics.Description: The number of entrances to your property measured as the first pageview in a session. Typically used with landingPagePath

Metrics.Name: Entrances / Pageviews
Metrics.Description: The percentage of pageviews in which this page was the entrance.

Metrics.Name: Event Value
Metrics.Description: The total value of events for the profile.

Metrics.Name: Events / Session with Event
Metrics.Description: The average number of events per session with event.

Metrics.Name: Exceptions
Metrics.Description: The number of exceptions that were sent to Google Analytics.

Metrics.Name: Exceptions / Screen
Metrics.Description: The number of exceptions thrown divided by the number of screenviews.

Metrics.Name: Exits
Metrics.Description: The number of exits from your property.

Metrics.Name: Goal Completions
Metrics.Description: The total number of completions for all goals defined for your profile.

Metrics.Name: Goal Conversion Rate
Metrics.Description: The percentage of sessions which resulted in a conversion to at least one of your goals.

Metrics.Name: Goal Starts
Metrics.Description: The total number of starts for all goals defined for your profile.

Metrics.Name: Goal Value
Metrics.Description: The total numeric value for all goals defined for your profile.

Metrics.Name: Goal XX Abandoned Funnels
Metrics.Description: The number of times users started conversion activity on the requested goal number without actually completing it.

Metrics.Name: Goal XX Abandonment Rate
Metrics.Description: The rate at which the requested goal number was abandoned.

Metrics.Name: Goal XX Completions
Metrics.Description: The total number of completions for the requested goal number.

Metrics.Name: Goal XX Conversion Rate
Metrics.Description: The percentage of sessions which resulted in a conversion to the requested goal number.

Metrics.Name: Goal XX Starts
Metrics.Description: The total number of starts for the requested goal number.

Metrics.Name: Goal XX Value
Metrics.Description: The total numeric value for the requested goal number.

Metrics.Name: Impressions
Metrics.Description: Total number of campaign impressions.

Metrics.Name: Internal Promotion Clicks
Metrics.Description: The number of clicks on an internal promotion (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Internal Promotion CTR
Metrics.Description: The rate at which users clicked through to view the internal promotion (ga:internalPromotionClicks / ga:internalPromotionViews) - (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Internal Promotion Views
Metrics.Description: The number of views of an internal promotion (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Local Product Refund Amount
Metrics.Description: Refund amount for a given product in the local currency (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Local Product Revenue
Metrics.Description: Product revenue in local currency.

Metrics.Name: Local Refund Amount
Metrics.Description: Total refund amount for the transaction in the local currency (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Local Revenue
Metrics.Description: Transaction revenue in local currency.

Metrics.Name: Local Shipping
Metrics.Description: Transaction shipping cost in local currency.

Metrics.Name: Local Tax
Metrics.Description: Transaction tax in local currency.

Metrics.Name: Margin
Metrics.Description: The overall transaction profit margin.

Metrics.Name: New Users
Metrics.Description: The number of users whose session on your property was marked as a first-time session.

Metrics.Name: Organic Searches
Metrics.Description: The number of organic searches that happened within a session. This metric is search engine agnostic.

Metrics.Name: Page Download Time (ms)
Metrics.Description: The total amount of time (in milliseconds) to download this page among all samples.

Metrics.Name: Page Load Sample
Metrics.Description: The sample set (or count) of pageviews used to calculate the average page load time.

Metrics.Name: Page Load Time (ms)
Metrics.Description: Total Page Load Time is the amount of time (in milliseconds) it takes for pages from the sample set to load, from initiation of the pageview (e.g. click on a page link) to load completion in the browser.

Metrics.Name: Page Value
Metrics.Description: The average value of this page or set of pages. Page Value is (ga:transactionRevenue + ga:goalValueAll) / ga:uniquePageviews (for the page or set of pages).

Metrics.Name: Pages / Session
Metrics.Description: The average number of pages viewed during a session on your property. Repeated views of a single page are counted.

Metrics.Name: Pageviews
Metrics.Description: The total number of pageviews for your property.

Metrics.Name: Per Search Goal Value
Metrics.Description: The average goal value of a search on your property.

Metrics.Name: Per Session Goal Value
Metrics.Description: The average goal value of a session on your property.

Metrics.Name: Per Session Value
Metrics.Description: Average transaction revenue for a session on your property.

Metrics.Name: Product Adds To Cart
Metrics.Description: Number of times the product was added to the shopping cart (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Product Checkouts
Metrics.Description: Number of times the product was included in the check-out process (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Product Detail Views
Metrics.Description: Number of times users viewed the product-detail page (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Product List Clicks
Metrics.Description: Number of times users clicked the product when it appeared in the product list (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Product List CTR
Metrics.Description: The rate at which users clicked through on the product in a product list (ga:productListClicks / ga:productListViews) - (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Product List Views
Metrics.Description: Number of times the product appeared in a product list (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Product Refund Amount
Metrics.Description: Total refund amount associated with the product (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Product Refunds
Metrics.Description: Number of times a refund was issued for the product (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Product Removes From Cart
Metrics.Description: Number of times the product was removed from shopping cart (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Product Revenue
Metrics.Description: The total revenue from purchased product items on your property.

Metrics.Name: Product Revenue per Purchase
Metrics.Description: Average product revenue per purchase (commonly used with Product Coupon Code) (ga:itemRevenue / ga:uniquePurchases) - (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Quantity
Metrics.Description: The total number of items purchased. For example, if users purchase 2 frisbees and 5 tennis balls, 7 items have been purchased.

Metrics.Name: Quantity Added To Cart
Metrics.Description: Number of product units added to the shopping cart (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Quantity Checked Out
Metrics.Description: Number of product units included in check out (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Quantity Refunded
Metrics.Description: Number of product units refunded (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Quantity Removed From Cart
Metrics.Description: Number of product units removed from cart (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Queried Product Quantity
Metrics.Description: Quantity of the product being queried.

Metrics.Name: Redirection Time (ms)
Metrics.Description: The total amount of time (in milliseconds) spent in redirects before fetching this page among all samples. If there are no redirects, the value for this metric is expected to be 0.

Metrics.Name: Refund Amount
Metrics.Description: Currency amount refunded for a transaction (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Refunds
Metrics.Description: Number of refunds that have been issued (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Metrics.Name: Related Product Quantity
Metrics.Description: Quantity of the related product.

Metrics.Name: Results Pageviews
Metrics.Description: The number of times a search result page was viewed after performing a search.

Metrics.Name: Results Pageviews / Search
Metrics.Description: The average number of times people viewed a search results page after performing a search.

Metrics.Name: Revenue
Metrics.Description: The total sale revenue provided in the transaction excluding shipping and tax.

Metrics.Name: ROI
Metrics.Description: Returns on Investment is overall transaction profit divided by derived advertising cost.

Metrics.Name: RPC
Metrics.Description: RPC or revenue-per-click is the average revenue (from ecommerce sales and/or goal value) you received for each click on one of your search ads.

Metrics.Name: Screen Views
Metrics.Description: The total number of screenviews.

Metrics.Name: Screens / Session
Metrics.Description: The average number of screenviews per session.

Metrics.Name: Search Depth
Metrics.Description: The average number of subsequent page views made on your property after a use of your internal search feature.

Metrics.Name: Search Exits
Metrics.Description: The number of exits on your site that occurred following a search result from your internal search feature.

Metrics.Name: Search Refinements
Metrics.Description: The total number of times a refinement (transition) occurs between internal search keywords within a session. For example if the sequence of keywords is: "shoes", "shoes", "pants", "pants", this metric will be one because the transition between "shoes" and "pants" is different.

Metrics.Name: Server Connection Time (ms)
Metrics.Description: The total amount of time (in milliseconds) spent in establishing TCP connection for this page among all samples.

Metrics.Name: Server Response Time (ms)
Metrics.Description: The total amount of time (in milliseconds) your server takes to respond to a user request among all samples, including the network time from user's location to your server.

Metrics.Name: Session Duration
Metrics.Description: The total duration of user sessions represented in total seconds.

Metrics.Name: Sessions
Metrics.Description: Counts the total number of sessions.

Metrics.Name: Sessions with Event
Metrics.Description: The total number of sessions with events.

Metrics.Name: Sessions with Search
Metrics.Description: The total number of sessions that included an internal search

Metrics.Name: Shipping
Metrics.Description: The total cost of shipping.

Metrics.Name: Site Search Goal Conversion Rate
Metrics.Description: The percentage of search sessions (i.e., sessions that included at least one search) which resulted in a conversion to at least one of your goals.

Metrics.Name: Site Search Goal XX Conversion Rate
Metrics.Description: The percentage of search sessions (i.e., sessions that included at least one search) which resulted in a conversion to the requested goal number.

Metrics.Name: Social Actions
Metrics.Description: The total number of social interactions on your property.

Metrics.Name: Speed Metrics Sample
Metrics.Description: The sample set (or count) of pageviews used to calculate the averages for site speed metrics. This metric is used in all site speed average calculations including avgDomainLookupTime, avgPageDownloadTime, avgRedirectionTime, avgServerConnectionTime, and avgServerResponseTime.

Metrics.Name: Tax
Metrics.Description: The total amount of tax.

Metrics.Name: Time after Search
Metrics.Description: The session duration on your property where a use of your internal search feature occurred.

Metrics.Name: Time after Search
Metrics.Description: The average amount of time people spent on your property after searching.

Metrics.Name: Time on Page
Metrics.Description: How long a user spent on a particular page in seconds. Calculated by subtracting the initial view time for a particular page from the initial view time for a subsequent page. Thus, this metric does not apply to exit pages for your property.

Metrics.Name: Time on Screen
Metrics.Description: The time spent viewing the current screen.

Metrics.Name: Total Abandonment Rate
Metrics.Description: The rate at which goals were abandoned.

Metrics.Name: Total Events
Metrics.Description: The total number of events for the profile, across all categories.

Metrics.Name: Total Unique Searches
Metrics.Description: The total number of unique keywords from internal searches within a session. For example if "shoes" was searched for 3 times in a session, it will be only counted once.

Metrics.Name: Total Value
Metrics.Description: Total value for your property (including total revenue and total goal value).

Metrics.Name: Transactions
Metrics.Description: The total number of transactions.

Metrics.Name: Unique Events
Metrics.Description: The total number of unique events for the profile, across all categories.

Metrics.Name: Unique Pageviews
Metrics.Description: The number of different (unique) pages within a session. This takes into account both the pagePath and pageTitle to determine uniqueness.

Metrics.Name: Unique Purchases
Metrics.Description: The number of product sets purchased. For example, if users purchase 2 frisbees and 5 tennis balls from your site, 2 unique products have been purchased.

Metrics.Name: Unique Screen Views
Metrics.Description: The number of different (unique) screenviews within a session.

Metrics.Name: Unique Social Actions
Metrics.Description: The number of sessions during which the specified social action(s) occurred at least once. This is based on the the unique combination of socialInteractionNetwork, socialInteractionAction, and socialInteractionTarget.

Metrics.Name: Unique Views
Metrics.Description: The number of different (unique) pages within a session for the specified content group. This takes into account both the pagePath and pageTitle to determine uniqueness.

Metrics.Name: User Timing (ms)
Metrics.Description: The total number of milliseconds for a user timing.

Metrics.Name: User Timing Sample
Metrics.Description: The number of hits that were sent for a particular userTimingCategory, userTimingLabel, and userTimingVariable.

Metrics.Name: Users
Metrics.Description: Total number of users to your property for the requested time period.

Metrics.Name: Time On Site
Metrics.Description: The total duration of visitor sessions represented in total seconds.
